79cf65d6-99be-4cf2-b328-4bbfb48da328	Tom Smith - TD - 1	Meeting ID: 8356\nMeeting Topic: Introductory Meeting Re: Optimize Wealth Platform\nHost Email: [EMAIL]\nStart Time (Eastern): 2025-12-03T12:59:01-05:00\n\n00:02:59.290 --> 00:03:00.510 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Hey, [ADVISOR]? 00:03:08.930 --> 00:03:10.289 [ADVISOR]: Hey, [OPTIMIZE_REP], how are you? 00:03:10.290 --> 00:03:11.869 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: I'm great, [ADVISOR], how are you? 00:03:11.870 --> 00:03:15.499 [ADVISOR]: Not too bad at all. My camera's just kicking on, there we go. 00:03:15.500 --> 00:03:17.290 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, there we go, now I can see you. 00:03:17.290 --> 00:03:17.850 [ADVISOR]: Perfect. 00:03:17.860 --> 00:03:19.150 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You doing well? 00:03:19.150 --> 00:03:20.760 [ADVISOR]: I can't complain, yeah. 00:03:20.760 --> 00:03:30.940 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: 100%, man, 100%. Before we begin, have you had a chance… so you've received the brochure from us? Yeah. Have you had a chance to review it? 00:03:30.940 --> 00:03:34.429 [ADVISOR]: I looked at it a little bit, yeah. It's been a couple weeks since I looked at it, though. 00:03:34.430 --> 00:03:38.820 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, okay, no problem. Did anything stand out when you first glanced at it? 00:03:38.820 --> 00:03:44.310 [ADVISOR]: From memory, nothing, no. 00:03:44.740 --> 00:04:09.590 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, no problem at all. Again, for the purposes of today's presentation, it's really, you know, I'll take the opportunity to really go through it at length, and again, provide you a, essentially a quick overview of our institutional asset management program here at Optimize, as well as our advisor platform. And then I'd like to, you know, at the end of it, just kind of get a brief overview of you and your practice. I have a small little fact find where we have, you know, half a dozen questions or so. 00:04:09.770 --> 00:04:15.879 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: But again, just to kind of really build that profile, of you and your business, if it goes well. 00:04:16.130 --> 00:04:18.100 [ADVISOR]: Optimized as a dealer, then, is that right? 00:04:18.100 --> 00:04:19.299 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's… that's correct. 00:04:19.300 --> 00:04:20.700 [ADVISOR]: Okay, understood. 00:04:20.709 --> 00:04:35.189 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's correct. And again, you know, just, just to kind of give you a brief background in terms of who we are and what it is that we do, you know, essentially our firm was founded in 2009, as a full-service global asset management firm. 00:04:35.190 --> 00:04:40.930 [ADVISOR]: Great time to start. Right after financial crisis. Or right in the middle of it. 00:04:40.930 --> 00:04:47.719 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Right in the middle of it, and coming out of it, I guess, right? And again, I'll signal out two dates. 00:04:47.830 --> 00:05:11.080 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That make this conversation a little bit more interesting. But again, in light of all the, you know, ashes in the industry, there's a lot of opportunity coming out of it. And, you know, this kind of signifies, not to say that that's what's happened here, but again, a lot of opportunity has presented itself, and again, the goal was to, you know, be a full-service global asset management firm. 00:05:11.080 --> 00:05:18.649 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: as well as providing institutional asset management, as well as family office services to its clients. And [ADVISOR]. 00:05:18.650 --> 00:05:29.119 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: about 5 years ago, so I would say probably closer to the end of 2019 or so, we created an opportunity for select premium advisors, to access our institutional platform. 00:05:29.400 --> 00:05:35.470 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Again, whether they're looking to scale their business, or essentially plan for their succession, right? 00:05:35.550 --> 00:05:59.210 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And what we found was that those advisors, you know, who passed our screening process, you know, immediately elevated their practice by gaining access to not only of our institutional investment program here at Optimize, but as well as our enhanced service offerings by way of our family office services, right? And again, this has quickly led us to become one of the fastest growing wealth management firms in Canada for the last 3 years. 00:05:59.210 --> 00:06:12.909 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You know, managing [AUM_AMOUNT] in assets under management. You know, we've onboarded [ADVISORY_TEAM_COUNT] advisory teams in the recent period alone, just to kind of, you know, paint that portrait in terms of the scale of our operations, okay? 00:06:12.930 --> 00:06:16.179 [ADVISOR]: Sorry, quick question, if I can just jump in. 00:06:16.180 --> 00:06:16.680 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Absolutely. 00:06:16.680 --> 00:06:27.459 [ADVISOR]: Do you have any familiarity with [CURRENT_DEALER] as a dealer, or [CURRENT_DEALER] Advisor? So there's [CURRENT_DEALER_BROKERAGE] on the, insurance side of. 00:06:27.460 --> 00:06:29.279 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Interesting short side, yep. 00:06:29.280 --> 00:06:33.759 [ADVISOR]: And then there's the [CURRENT_DEALER_CHANNEL] as well, is what we're called, the old [PREDECESSOR_FIRM], basically. 00:06:33.760 --> 00:06:34.960 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: The old [PREDECESSOR_FIRM], yep. 00:06:34.960 --> 00:06:38.439 [ADVISOR]: Are you familiar with the difference between the two? 00:06:39.120 --> 00:06:40.900 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: I have a rough understanding of it. Okay, of course. 00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:57.500 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, and so which side of that barrier would you say you lie? You're a career sales force? Yes. Okay. And again, you know, I get into a lot of conversations with [CURRENT_DEALER] Advisors, pertaining mainly to their contract and their… 00:06:57.500 --> 00:06:57.940 [ADVISOR]: But I was joking. 00:06:57.940 --> 00:07:02.260 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, no, no, I like to disclose it right up front, in their… 00:07:02.740 --> 00:07:16.119 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: quote-unquote inability, to transition, right, out of [CURRENT_DEALER]. And I… I kind of… I don't want to say poke holes to that, but ultimately, just referencing the fact that, 00:07:16.210 --> 00:07:31.580 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, I like to impart a question and say, you know, how are you paid, right? In that contract, are you earning a salary, right? And if the answer to that question is no, and it's purely commission-based, and I know who. 00:07:31.580 --> 00:07:33.450 [ADVISOR]: We can do what we want at the end of the day. 00:07:33.450 --> 00:07:54.479 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Right, absolutely, and I think that's just kind of an awareness, [ADVISOR], that most advisors within [CURRENT_DEALER] just kind of don't grasp, and it is a walled garden, I'll attest to that, right? And [CURRENT_DEALER] does a really good job of keeping their advisors within that walled garden. You know, they put a barbed wire fence all along the edge of it, so you can't even poke your head to see what's out there, right? 00:07:54.480 --> 00:07:56.230 [ADVISOR]: They do, but I have gloves to climb the fence. 00:07:56.230 --> 00:08:02.529 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, and a thick blanket to put it over. Hopefully, right? 00:08:02.530 --> 00:08:05.089 [ADVISOR]: So, I didn't want to interrupt, I just wanted to… 00:08:05.090 --> 00:08:24.659 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, no, no, that's fair, absolutely. I have a great understanding of what the conversation looks like, and [ADVISOR], I'm glad that we're here today kind of expanding on that notion, right? And again, just to mention that we are not, you know, a retail investment dealer, you know, offering the retail product shelf environment to the retail channel, right? 00:08:24.660 --> 00:08:35.440 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: We are an institutional money manager looking to, you know, exclusively partner with, you know, premium advisors in the industry, you know, who are ready to move beyond that kind of space, right? 00:08:35.610 --> 00:09:00.599 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And again, we're looking to work with, you know, those advisors who want to take their practice to the next level, okay? And I'll kind of just guide you through this presentation in terms of the key elements that do stand out, you know, and by all means, you know, if there are questions, I will pause to be able to kind of effectively help answer any of the questions that you have, or see if you have any questions, but if something does come up, by all means, please introduce 00:09:00.600 --> 00:09:01.400 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: reject. 00:09:02.260 --> 00:09:26.969 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, at Optimize, you know, we offer a, you know, completely independent… we are completely independent, right? We kind of pride ourselves on that notion, you know, allowing us to offer, essentially, an entrepreneurial culture in which to operate in. You know, one that is purely fixated on your goals and objectives, [ADVISOR]. You know, and unlike many other firms out there who are being built, just to be sold to some, you know, private equity firm or to a bank. 00:09:27.440 --> 00:09:31.110 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You know, there's absolutely no intention to sell the business from our end. 00:09:31.130 --> 00:09:46.209 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So you can be certain that moving your business over to optimize, you know, won't result you in having to, you know, reevaluate things at some premature later point, right? Just because, you know, the founders of the company wanted to or needed to cash out, and… 00:09:46.210 --> 00:10:08.900 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You kind of get left wondering who you partner with in the first place, right? So, but that being said, you know, we're leveraging our independence through our global financial strength of our custodian, which is [CUSTODIAN], and by far and away the largest custodian in Canada, you know, [CUSTODIAN_AUM] in assets under management, [CUSTODIAN_INVESTOR_COUNT] Canadian investors, so you kind of get the best of both worlds here at Optimize, you know, that complete independence. 00:10:08.900 --> 00:10:12.599 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You know, that's coupled with absolute bank-level security on the other end, right? 00:10:13.250 --> 00:10:14.450 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And… and… 00:10:14.450 --> 00:10:37.970 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, just to kind of jump in, you know, these are some of the key elements in terms of our value proposition in terms of how we go out to attract advisors. And surely, you know, our compensation structure is, you know, fully reflective of this. It is one that is, you know, fully equitable and transparent for all our advisors. And again, it has three key components, right? 00:10:38.150 --> 00:10:42.100 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And before I get into those three key components, which you'll see is kind of. 00:10:42.100 --> 00:10:43.669 [ADVISOR]: There's no grid level, basically. 00:10:43.670 --> 00:10:49.549 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: no grid level, right? And we realize that the retail dealer model has advisors on grids, you know, has advisors on… 00:10:49.710 --> 00:11:05.780 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, payouts that are getting, you know, squeezed or disproportionately favoring, you know, one advisor over another based on production, right? We know this to be true, right? And so that being said, you know, transition bonus. First and foremost, it's the first key element. We're saying to you. 00:11:05.920 --> 00:11:06.700 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Go ahead. 00:11:06.980 --> 00:11:10.049 [ADVISOR]: Just… I don't know if… 00:11:10.050 --> 00:11:10.710 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Shoot. 00:11:10.710 --> 00:11:19.740 [ADVISOR]: I'm just thinking out loud here, if I'm… If you're looking for, Premier Advisors. 00:11:19.740 --> 00:11:20.430 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yep. 00:11:20.870 --> 00:11:23.700 [ADVISOR]: And… We're talking. 00:11:24.040 --> 00:11:24.400 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yep. 00:11:24.400 --> 00:11:26.909 [ADVISOR]: I'm on the higher end of the grid level. 00:11:27.060 --> 00:11:32.409 [ADVISOR]: Don't I like the grid level? Don't I like the grid system? Don't I like getting comped more? 00:11:32.910 --> 00:11:39.499 [ADVISOR]: than somebody else. So if you're looking for somebody like me, I don't know, that's just… 00:11:39.500 --> 00:11:54.359 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, yeah, that's a thought process for sure, of course, and that's… that's… that's… and I respect that. That's something that you've, fully come to expect in terms of a reality, right? In terms of being at the higher threshold of that grid structure within [CURRENT_DEALER]. 00:11:54.360 --> 00:12:18.180 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And again, that being said, you know, that's, you know, pat yourself on the back, right? And it's like reading a good book. You're at… if you're at a chapter, you know, you're at an end of a chapter, in which you've really enjoyed it, well, stay tuned, because the next chapter, you know, that's kind of the analogy I like to say in response to that argument, because all we're saying is you're turning a leaf, or turning a page, and going into that next chapter. 00:12:18.180 --> 00:12:30.759 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And [ADVISOR], like, honestly, the opposite isn't true, right? The opposite, where an advisor comes from a dealer who's not happy, is disenchanted with the. 00:12:30.760 --> 00:12:32.579 [ADVISOR]: I'm not saying I'm happy, I'm just saying… 00:12:32.580 --> 00:12:33.549 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, no, of course, of course. 00:12:33.550 --> 00:12:35.550 [ADVISOR]: Better than some others in the company, right? 00:12:35.550 --> 00:12:36.180 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course. 00:12:36.180 --> 00:12:41.730 [ADVISOR]: And that, in and of itself, creates an opportunity for me to go partner with these other advisors. 00:12:41.730 --> 00:12:42.420 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course. 00:12:42.420 --> 00:12:45.429 [ADVISOR]: Spread there and just swallow books, right? 00:12:45.430 --> 00:12:56.159 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course, and this is for you to… and again, this is why this discussion is exploratory, it's our introduction, right, in terms of what our platform can do over and above 00:12:56.190 --> 00:13:11.180 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And again, this is something that you take away, right? And be able to really conceptualize and review on your end and say, well, what's the right move for me, right? I can't help answer that. I can only give you the tools to be able to come up with that assessment. Ultimately, I'm gonna… 00:13:11.180 --> 00:13:32.599 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: We know what that competitive landscape is. You know, our compensation structure surely is reflective of one that is not only competitive, but industry leading in that sense. And we know this to be true. Like, we've… we've onboarded advisors coming from, you know, a myriad of financial institutions, if you will, right? 00:13:32.600 --> 00:13:34.969 [ADVISOR]: What… what do I do with my insurance book? 00:13:35.710 --> 00:13:42.290 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So, that's a great question. So, your insurance book stays as is, right? that being said… 00:13:42.290 --> 00:13:43.850 [ADVISOR]: [CURRENT_DEALER] would can me. 00:13:44.350 --> 00:13:59.040 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Not necessarily. Not necessarily. So what we're saying is, you know, on that… so first and foremost, it's kind of two-pronged. Obviously, we wouldn't stay at [CURRENT_DEALER], if that's the answer to your question. So we have partnered with our MGA, which is [MGA]. 00:13:59.040 --> 00:14:08.420 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And so, mo… most… all of that insurance book would be transferred to our partner, through our MGA [MGA], okay? 00:14:08.850 --> 00:14:12.999 [ADVISOR]: No. I don't own it. I don't own it. [CURRENT_DEALER] does. 00:14:13.770 --> 00:14:16.460 [ADVISOR]: That's why I asked if you were familiar with the structure. 00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:19.869 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, no, of course I am, but again, in terms of… 00:14:19.870 --> 00:14:25.240 [ADVISOR]: I can't move my insurance with me. They have to… Well… 00:14:26.330 --> 00:14:27.300 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's again. 00:14:27.300 --> 00:14:27.850 [ADVISOR]: It was a reason. 00:14:27.850 --> 00:14:28.500 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: One thing I challenge. 00:14:28.500 --> 00:14:29.540 [ADVISOR]: Actually, yeah… 00:14:29.690 --> 00:14:30.659 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: with the… 00:14:30.660 --> 00:14: