%, maybe my lingo was off, you get that full 5%, 00:23:39.310 --> 00:23:41.309 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: If it's 5 years or more. 00:23:41.310 --> 00:23:41.790 [ADVISOR]: Gotcha. 00:23:41.790 --> 00:24:06.730 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: tenured, okay? Understood. And again, at a prorated rate, as this table… if you decide to leave the business within the first year, right, and retire, the succession payout is half that. And again, still kind of compelling. 2.5% versus 2.5 times that revenue valuation is a slightly greater number. 5% definitely is at that 10-year marker, which represents a 00:24:06.730 --> 00:24:12.530 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: significant amount of value. And again, kind of, you know, the do-nothing, state your current retail dealer approach. 00:24:12.530 --> 00:24:35.379 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, just shy of [PROJECTED_REVENUE_AMOUNT] in terms of revenue. We're saying at optimized over that 10-year period. I want to say double, but it's not. But, it's just a little over [PROJECTED_REVENUE_AMOUNT]. And again, presents an opportunity of [VALUE_DIFFERENCE_AMOUNT] being left on the table, right? So again, going back to your discussion in terms of what can I do? Obviously, it's… I know that was more so a rhetorical question. 00:24:35.380 --> 00:24:51.189 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: I don't necessarily have the answer to that question, unfortunately. You'd have to look at your contract and try and poke holes yourself in terms of what can be done first and foremost on that insurance business, but knowing full well that, yes, we do have a platform that can facilitate 00:24:51.190 --> 00:25:07.699 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And again, you can continue to write a new insurance business through our platform, right? And again, realizing that most advisors, most, I mean, not bank advisors, but most advisors from the independent channel, or that are coming from the insurance companies, are dual licensed in that regard, right? 00:25:08.640 --> 00:25:23.960 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And again, it's just really kind of showcasing, you know, the potential savings on fees. We know that, you know, from our end, you know, first and foremost, we know that the retail dealer model charges, for example, for… 00:25:23.960 --> 00:25:48.939 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: annual administration fees for registered accounts. They might charge you for equity trading or mutual fund trading fees. They charge desk fees, right? And so we're saying there's none of that on our platform. And so, you know, you can be certain that joining Optimize, you won't have to pay a technology or desk fee, or any marketing fees, or any, you know, account-related fees. There are no transaction costs on any of our Optimize funds. 00:25:50.140 --> 00:25:53.000 [ADVISOR]: Does that mean I don't pay them, or the client doesn't pay them? 00:25:53.170 --> 00:25:58.110 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You don't pay them. I can tell you what the fees are at the account, and fund level. 00:25:58.110 --> 00:26:02.350 [ADVISOR]: Like, I don't think I pay anything right now for any of these to begin with. 00:26:02.350 --> 00:26:18.650 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, and that's great. And that potential savings on fee would be zero. Yeah, okay. In most cases, when I get into a conversation, I'm kind of shocked where there might be some desk fees associated. And again, with this example. 00:26:18.650 --> 00:26:22.730 [ADVISOR]: I have to rent my office space, but that's up to me, because I'm not in the branch, but I could… 00:26:22.730 --> 00:26:24.440 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course, like a regional office. 00:26:24.440 --> 00:26:25.290 [ADVISOR]: Yeah. 00:26:25.290 --> 00:26:30.870 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Right. But when you were in a regional office, did you… Was there a fee to… 00:26:30.870 --> 00:26:33.099 [ADVISOR]: I had to pay for my office, yeah. 00:26:33.270 --> 00:26:34.300 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay. 00:26:34.300 --> 00:26:36.050 [ADVISOR]: Nothing to trade, there's no… no, no. 00:26:36.050 --> 00:26:51.599 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, yeah, no, that's fair, that's fair, understood. And again, 