_REP]: Okay, so Nesto, again, it's… everything is done in a very centralized way through online prep and submission forms. Nesto is a big, I guess, Canadian aggregator, if you will. It's a… 00:31:18.670 --> 00:31:26.760 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You know, it helps facilitate the loans and mortgage discussion for financial planners, you know, who've migrated to that platform. 00:31:26.760 --> 00:31:28.880 [ADVISOR]: Do you find much leveraging going on? 00:31:29.520 --> 00:31:30.120 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: in… 00:31:30.120 --> 00:31:32.140 [ADVISOR]: invest within that… 00:31:33.010 --> 00:31:36.950 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So… Again, you said it best, right? 00:31:37.380 --> 00:31:46.180 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: the one-stop shop, where now everything is coming under one roof, right? Instead of now you having a, you know, center of influence where you're… 00:31:46.180 --> 00:32:10.450 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: piecemealing, you say, I'll take care of your insurance business, and I'll take care of your wealth business, but, you know, I'm not able to do tax planning or give you any strategies there. I'm not able to do, you know, loans or mortgages. Now, you're kind of centered in that discussion, right? And it's giving you… and not to say that… listen, we're not here to step on toes. If clients have existing relationships with, you know, tax professionals or, you know, accountants or lawyers, by all means, continue with those 00:32:10.450 --> 00:32:32.690 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: This is just the value add to say, hey, listen, you no longer need to do any of that. We can see if we can kind of centralize it. If there are more complex, you know, loan arrangements to be made, then obviously, you know, that might be going back to their own bank, for example, or someone who they've been dealing with. But again, this is just a more value add to be able to centralize it to your business. 00:32:32.690 --> 00:32:36.679 [ADVISOR]: To this day, I have no idea. [FINANCIAL_INSTITUTION] did it. [FINANCIAL_INSTITUTION]. 00:32:37.300 -->