al, you know, our institutional fund portfolios, our models, if you will, right? 00:34:05.210 --> 00:34:07.930 [ADVISOR]: That gives me, the advisor, a better chance to quarterback it. 00:34:08.190 --> 00:34:09.480 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course. Yeah, yeah. 00:34:09.489 --> 00:34:15.709 [ADVISOR]: I passed referrals off to [FINANCIAL_INSTITUTION] before, and the rep no-showed my client, and my client's mad at me for the [FINANCIAL_INSTITUTION] rep not. 00:34:15.710 --> 00:34:16.420 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course. 00:34:16.420 --> 00:34:19.460 [ADVISOR]: So, I'd like to take that out if possible. 00:34:19.469 --> 00:34:34.569 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course, and this is kind of the platform that will help you. Obviously, this is new, right? And most advisors who have transitioned, it's just a value add, right? They've come to really appreciate that level of service, if you will, right? 00:34:34.570 --> 00:34:35.150 [ADVISOR]: Yep. 00:34:35.350 --> 00:34:58.450 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And again, really showcasing the strength, you know, looking at that example that I provided in terms of that advisor with the [BOOK_SIZE_AMOUNT] book. Obviously, it's a hypothetical advisor, we've made some key assumptions, but really showcasing that, you know, over the… from a client's perspective now, we've really covered the, you know, the compensation component for the advisor in terms of what they could earn. 00:34:58.450 --> 00:35:23.389 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: But really now, flipping the script and saying, okay, for that same advisor on our platform, what does it look like, right? And again, from the client's perspective, over the same 10-year period, we're saying that you could receive an additional [INCREMENTAL_VALUE_AMOUNT] in potential incremental value through, you know, our family office services, right? When you factor in your, you know, the financial planning, the will and tax practice that have a cost associated to 00:35:23.390 --> 00:35:47.490 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And what we've able to do, just to really be able to quantify and measure what those, you know, ancillary costs are with each, you know, client, with each plan, with each, you know, tax return, and project it over time. Again, it becomes a substantial value in terms of cost savings, right, or potential value from 00:35:47.490 --> 00:35:52.710 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, being now offering these types of services, right? So we're saying. 00:35:52.710 --> 00:35:54.700 [ADVISOR]: And you know what I like? I'm sorry to interrupt. 00:35:54.700 --> 00:35:55.379 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, no, no, go for it. 00:35:55.380 --> 00:35:59.209 [ADVISOR]: I like there's no… there's no star anywhere on this page, there's no asterisk. 00:35:59.210 --> 00:36:02.419 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So at the very… at the very, very least. 00:36:02.490 --> 00:36:06.890 [ADVISOR]: Your compliance department is… is… is okay with me. 00:36:06.890 --> 00:36:07.430 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course! 00:36:07.430 --> 00:36:09.279 [ADVISOR]: I shouldn't let this go through without any of that. 00:36:09.280 --> 00:36:10.080 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course. 00:36:10.080 --> 00:36:17.229 [ADVISOR]: That's a different world than what I'm used to. I can't send an email without compliance looking at it, so not that I have to do anything wrong or anything. 00:36:17.230 --> 00:36:37.050 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, no, no, of course, of course. And again, just… and again, and I respect that, and it's an understanding that it's a very, kind of, regulated space, right? For us to be able to run that content has to… and again, we have a compliance department, and we're very… we operate in the same regulatory framework as [CURRENT_DEALER], as any other dealer. 00:36:37.050 --> 00:36:38.220 [ADVISOR]: interprets… 00:36:38.220 --> 00:36:38.800 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course. 00:36:38.800 --> 00:36:40.869 [ADVISOR]: A little bit differently than most. 00:36:40.870 --> 00:36:47.280 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Of course, and they're like, okay, less. Less is more, right? And so they don't want to give you that ammunition. 00:36:47.280 --> 00:36:50.220 [ADVISOR]: Yeah, I feel like we're herded cattle, just following. 00:36:50.400 --> 00:36:52.270 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: For sure. 00:36:52.270 --> 00:36:55.660 [ADVISOR]: Every once in a while, the cows know what they're doing, just let them be. 00:36:55.660 --> 00:37:18.610 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Let them do, yeah, yeah, yeah, exactly. That's a great analogy, but that's it. And again, what we're trying to say here, I've taken potential fund performance out of the equation for now. What we're saying, this might be zero, I showcased it in a previous slide, but again, no annual administration, equity, and mutual fund trading fees. When you start quantifying an average number for an advisory practice. 00:37:18.740 --> 00:37:38.180 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: and projected over a course of time, it's a quite significant number and potentially quite significant savings on our end, right? So when you factor in now the potential outperformance of any of our models over that time, again, this is a historical snapshot, looking back at a 10-year performance, if you will. 00:37:38.180 --> 00:37:51.950 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: of our models, obviously no crystal ball, it's not projected outwards, but this is kind of what our, you know, outperformances look like relative to our benchmark in that 10-year space. 00:37:51.950 --> 00:37:52.660 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay. 00:37:53.810 --> 00:37:57.719 [ADVISOR]: So this… wait, so this is talking about market fund performance? 00:37:57.720 --> 00:38:01.849 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: This is talking about fund performance, yeah, and again, I wanted to. 00:38:01.850 --> 00:38:07.750 [ADVISOR]: What is an all-growth optimized Portfolio look like? 00:38:09.100 --> 00:38:11.880 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: In terms of, like, performance? 00:38:14.870 --> 00:38:17.939 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: In terms of holdings, in terms of… 00:38:18.340 --> 00:38:22.689 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So on all growth, I'm looking at it right now, I can give you. 00:38:22.690 --> 00:38:29.639 [ADVISOR]: We're talking about optimized outperformance 2.39, it says, for all growth, for example, right? Yep. So… 00:38:29.640 --> 00:38:30.260 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: this is… 00:38:30.450 --> 00:38:33.760 [ADVISOR]: What is performing, and what is it outperforming? 00:38:34.610 --> 00:38:47.919 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So, that's a great question. It's, it's performing, if I look at… so I'm looking at the fund profile itself. This is to assume a specific breakdown. So, we ask the advisor… So there's, like. 00:38:47.920 --> 00:38:52.220 [ADVISOR]: one code for the all-growth, or it's just… There's a… there's a 100%. 00:38:52.220 --> 00:38:52.720 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, buddy. 00:38:52.720 --> 00:38:54.250 [ADVISOR]: Portfolio or something. 00:38:54.250 --> 00:39:02.800 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, it is a fund code, and it is a fund-to-fund solution, if you will. It has top 10 holdings, I mean, we've done well. 00:39:03.030 --> 00:39:05.520 [ADVISOR]: Okay, so it's a portfolio, it's a fund of… 00:39:05.520 --> 00:39:20.770 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: It's a fund of funds managed internally. We have access to institutional portfolio managers that, again, help us construct this portfolio, right? Everything is done internally, of course, but again, when we get to, 00:39:21.160 --> 00:39:25.490 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You know, talking about the funds in terms of, you know, what they are, you know. 00:39:25.490 --> 00:39:32.000 [ADVISOR]: So, can I still, buy Fidelity funds, for example, or sell Fidelity funds, for example? 00:39:32.180 --> 00:39:40.890 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So that's… that's the note I'd like to touch on, and the answer to that question is, a no, because it is a proprietary model, right? 00:39:40.890 --> 00:39:44.280 [ADVISOR]: Just a realization that… I was gonna say, where's all this extra money coming from? 00:39:44.280 --> 00:39:53.609 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Right, it's a proprietary fund model, right? And again, it's our own in-house fund models, and again, 5 portfolio solutions, as you saw, from income all the way to growth, all growth. 00:39:53.610 --> 00:39:59.590 [ADVISOR]: So there's only 5… I don't want to say fund posts, because there's corporate class… maybe? Is there corporate class on the bridge? 00:39:59.590 --> 00:40:00.200 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yo. 00:40:00.200 --> 00:40:01.420 [ADVISOR]: No corporate class for now. 00:40:01.420 --> 00:40:03.270 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: corporate class. Yeah, and that's fine. 00:40:03.270 --> 00:40:04.300 [ADVISOR]: we're targeting. 00:40:04.590 --> 00:40:05.800 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's correct. 00:40:06.730 --> 00:40:08.829 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Sorry, the market that we're targeting? 00:40:08.830 --> 00:40:16.600 [ADVISOR]: The market we're targeting is non-REG funds, really, because we want people that have maxed out their RRSPs and maxed out their TFSAs and have nowhere else to put it but non-REG. 00:40:16.600 --> 00:40:17.159 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, no, no. 00:40:17.160 --> 00:40:18.370 [ADVISOR]: Gotcha. 00:40:18.370 --> 00:40:18.970 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Perfectly. 00:40:19.640 --> 00:40:26.030 [ADVISOR]: Part of a real tool to help that market is corporate class funds, but we don't have any, and we're trying to target that market, is that right? 00:40:26.030 --> 00:40:26.850 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's correct. 00:40:26.850 --> 00:40:27.720 [ADVISOR]: Okay. 00:40:27.910 --> 00:40:36.659 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, we do not have… and again, our philosophy there has been, you know, some of the structures that have been long-standing within corporate class funds have been eroded. Yeah. 00:40:36.660 --> 00:41:00.739 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: closed loopholes, or whatever that might be, through successive budget announcements, and so a big foray into offering a corporate class fund and potentially creating a different cost structure, didn't seem viable internally to pursue, okay? And again, from our end, you know, just really looking at it, holistically and, 00:41:00.740 --> 00:41:04.130 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You know, when we talk about, 00:41:04.250 --> 00:41:27.840 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: