Gotcha. 00:40:07.440 --> 00:40:21.730 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah. But just to revisit, our… at our core, at the core of our approach, really these three, you know, foundational components. They just, they work together, they drive long-term results for clients. 00:40:21.730 --> 00:40:28.579 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And they're really the backbone of how we manage and build and manage our portfolios. So, 00:40:28.580 --> 00:40:46.960 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: stringent, security selection, dynamic asset allocation, and, pension-style assets, or the strategic diversification. So, it really defines the institutional discipline behind everything we do. So the first thing, again, the, 00:40:47.720 --> 00:40:57.209 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: is the… that strong emphasis we have on high quality, you know, the solid public companies. That solid, 00:40:57.640 --> 00:41:01.620 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: High-quality, global, large-cap public companies. 00:41:01.720 --> 00:41:10.159 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: We're focused on businesses, of course, durable balance sheet, consistent earnings, sustainable competitive advantage, all the things you know. 00:41:10.160 --> 00:41:17.629 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And it's… it's that discipline selection process. It's really the cornerstone of how we build stability and deliver risk-adjusted 00:41:17.630 --> 00:41:31.150 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: returns over the long term, up to 80% of every portfolio, right? Second is that dynamic asset allocation, so rather than relying on, of course, static portfolio mixes, we're actively adjusting exposures based on 00:41:31.150 --> 00:41:40.109 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You know, all the obvious components, prevailing market conditions, valuation trends, broader economic cycles. 00:41:40.270 --> 00:41:58.730 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: allows us to really position portfolios more effectively as conditions change. So we're capturing opportunity when it's present, and we're mitigating risk when it's warranted. And that goes back, and we'll talk about this a little bit more, but to that, talking a