 can only work with what you have access to, right? And so, you know, when you don't have access to institutional product, it's that you work with what you have, right? And so I know that this will be definitely a benefit, no matter which way we kind of slice it. 00:51:48.820 --> 00:52:08.360 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: I'm going to suggest to you that, you know, normally this is sort of a much more drawn-out process, but I'm going to suggest to you that, we think about booking something for, that mutual due diligence that I was talking about, you know, where you come into the office and, 00:52:08.360 --> 00:52:18.039 [ADVISOR]: There's 4 folks there that do, like, key leaders that do presentations on the portfolio management side a little more robustly, right? And on the transition program. 00:52:18.040 --> 00:52:30.990 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: on the marketing and advisor marketing programs, and then also on the tech piece. So what I'm gonna do is this. Let's, look at calendars while we're together here. I'm going to send you. 00:52:30.990 --> 00:52:33.279 [ADVISOR]: Well, you actually already have this. 00:52:33.360 --> 00:52:34.250 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: the… 00:52:34.420 --> 00:52:51.369 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: technology platform and the transition program were two of the links that you would have been sent? Yes. Okay, so what I'm going to suggest to you is this. Let's book… let's book tran… let's book a due diligence day, and but I'm going to treat it as if we've already 00:52:51.520 --> 00:52:58.189 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: talk… we've already had another call with the transition deck. You can review those, and those will be easy for you, so… 00:52:58.580 --> 00:53:16.479 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Let's look at calendars here. It's a half, it's a half day. It's specifically for you, it's not a… there's not a cohort of people that come in for this, so we do it specifically around you. The meeting starts at 9.30 in the morning, goes till about 1. We have a little bit of a working lunch, you know, sort of throughou