w, help you. We can furnish things. I mean, we can do all kinds of… we have all kinds of resources, so… 00:57:59.090 --> 00:57:59.700 [ADVISOR]: Yeah. 00:57:59.700 --> 00:58:03.750 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Whatever help you need. It strikes me that you may not need much help in anything. 00:58:03.750 --> 00:58:04.680 [ADVISOR]: 20 pajamas. 00:58:04.680 --> 00:58:07.089 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: I say that in a very complimentary way. 00:58:07.090 --> 00:58:18.329 [ADVISOR]: I would only say that it would be more of a matter of if I really needed to escalate things, you know, because of whatever reason, it's like, then I might reach out for some support, but otherwise, yeah, I've usually got a handle on… 00:58:18.530 --> 00:58:21.110 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, so we've got that whole transition. 00:58:21.110 --> 00:58:26.540 [ADVISOR]: Yeah, I don't think there's any questions here that I won't… wouldn't be covered in the due diligence day, so… yeah. 00:58:26.540 --> 00:58:28.830 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, that's the best time to really… 00:58:28.830 --> 00:58:29.520 [ADVISOR]: Yeah. 00:58:29.520 --> 00:58:42.120 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: We get everything out during that point. The one thing… one question I should ask you, just because it'll… it's a checkmark in a box somewhere, is from a regulatory standpoint, ever any issues from a regulatory standpoint, sanctions, anything like that? 00:58:42.120 --> 00:58:45.099 [ADVISOR]: No, I've never had a complaint or anything. 00:58:45.100 --> 00:58:58.599 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's fine. It's just one of the questions you get asked down the road at some point, but… Yeah, yeah, no, they were an issue. Okay, well then, what I'm going to say is that this is, you know, this is all I've got for you today. 00:58:58.600 --> 00:58:59.520 [ADVISOR]: No, that's great. 00:58:59.520 --> 00:59:04.679 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, look for, you're gonna be, somebody will reach out. 00:59:04.830 --> 00:59:11.750 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: on our team, regarding the travel arrangements. We'll look forward to seeing you, on the 18th, or the 19th. 00:59:11.750 --> 00:59:12.770 [ADVISOR]: You there as well? 00:59:12.770 --> 00:59:20.010 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, I'll be there as well, and I'll probably have [CORPORATE_DEVELOPMENT_LEAD] will come in. [CORPORATE_DEVELOPMENT_LEAD] is, a tremendous… he's a… he's, 00:59:20.010 --> 00:59:37.239 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: the, head of corporate development, and he's portfolio manager by training, he'll be there as well, and there just isn't a question that you won't be able to have answered during that session, and I'm sure there's, you know, it'll be… it's an interactive session too, right? 00:59:37.240 --> 00:59:50.749 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, perfect, yeah. Yeah, we'll look forward to it. If there are any questions you have in the meantime, feel free to reach out, and otherwise, we'll just put, we'll get the wheels turning, and we'll see you on the 19th here. 00:59:50.750 --> 00:59:52.709 [ADVISOR]: Sounds great. Thanks so much for your time. 00:59:52.710 --> 00:59:53.979 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You bet, [ADVISOR], you too. 00:59:53.980 --> 00:59:55.740 [ADVISOR]: Looking forward to meeting you in person. 00:59:56.020 --> 00:59:56.770 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you. 00:59:57.060 --> 00:59:59.210 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, thanks so much. Take care. You too. Bye for now.	completed	2026-05-22 02:02:25.373213+00	2026-05-22 02:03:27.863439+00	\N	\N
e59639f8-41b9-4f14-a5d8-f8ab3ee0abb0	David Miller - Black Rock - 3	Meeting ID: 87586057720\nMeeting Topic: Follow-up Meeting Re: Optimize Transition Program and Technology Platform\nHost Email: [EMAIL]\nStart Time (Eastern): 2025-12-12T12:48:16-05:00\n\n00:10:56.080 --> 00:10:57.710 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Hey, [ADVISOR], how's it going? 00:10:58.780 --> 00:11:02.780 [ADVISOR]: Just making sure… can you hear me okay? I was having little issues with my audio earlier. 00:11:02.780 --> 00:11:04.280 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, yeah, you're coming in loud and clear. 00:11:04.280 --> 00:11:05.450 [ADVISOR]: Okay, perfect. 00:11:05.450 --> 00:11:06.859 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Perfect, perfect. 00:11:07.280 --> 00:11:08.779 [ADVISOR]: Okay, how's your week been? 00:11:08.780 --> 00:11:17.149 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, it's been pretty good, been pretty busy, which is always nice. Makes the days go by faster, but yeah, it's been pretty receptive, leading up to Christmas, so… 00:11:17.150 --> 00:11:23.809 [ADVISOR]: Yeah, that's good, that's good, and it's always nice to be leading into the weekend, and soon the holidays, so. 00:11:23.980 --> 00:11:40.399 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Are you all done your Christmas shopping for family and friends? I haven't even started. I think I have one gift, so, yeah, Monday morning, I'm gonna spend my… I'm gonna take an hour on my lunch and just hit the mall and drain my bank account, so… How about yourself? 00:11:40.400 --> 00:11:52.689 [ADVISOR]: Yeah, you know, I mean, it's mostly about my son and getting him all the little things, and then if there's anyone left over, I'm sure I can find that next week. But I think all my son's stuff is done. 00:11:52.690 --> 00:11:53.240 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: In fact. 00:11:53.240 --> 00:11:53.860 [ADVISOR]: workers. 00:11:54.050 --> 00:11:55.240 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's good, that's good. 00:11:55.340 --> 00:12:14.689 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, so for today, as you're well aware, we're going to be talking about our transition program, the efficiencies behind that program and how it works, as well, take a preview into our technology stack that we put together for your practice, and then this way you can easily transition using that technology stack, as well as manage your practice on a go-forward basis. 00:12:14.690 --> 00:12:15.490 [ADVISOR]: Great. 00:12:16.190 --> 00:12:34.370 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And so, in terms of our technology program that we put in place, we really like to take a very dynamic approach to the required time to transition any advisor, and so the reason we keep the timeline so dynamic is that we want to structure the start and finish dates completely around your particular situation. 00:12:34.370 --> 00:12:42.889 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: As opposed to any kind of rigid, predefined timelines. And so, at a high level, our transition program has 4 key stages. 00:12:42.940 --> 00:12:44.170 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And so… 00:12:48.750 --> 00:13:05.940 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And so, how we ensure that we have a successful transition is that, again, it's always very centered, a very well-defined timeline, ensures everybody knows what's responsible, who's responsible for what, and, so this way, leading up to the transition, everybody's kind of on the same page here. 00:13:06.340 --> 00:13:24.339 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Now, the first stage of the transition is the initial setup stage. This is where you'll be assigned and will meet your transition manager. This is where you'll get all of your key optimized contacts. You'll be able to introduce us to your team, and perhaps most importantly, we'll go through the customized transition project plan that we have designed for you and your team. 00:13:26.660 --> 00:13:40.809 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And so, the second stage is, so this transition project plan is really centered, around your transition. It will spell out things like the various deliverables on both sides of the project. You'll be able to see Gantt charts, 00:13:41.180 --> 00:13:58.240 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: deadlines on milestones, such as when you'll need to get us your client data, or, or when we need to bring you in for headshots for your website or team branding and things like that. And this is so that you can all start and finish your transition on time, if not a little bit ahead of schedule. 00:14:00.410 --> 00:14:12.859 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And then next is the marketing and branding stage. As the name suggests, this is where our marketing team will design and create your team's branding, your team's website, as well as all of the ongoing client and prospecting content, again, fully branded to you. 00:14:15.200 --> 00:14:33.929 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And then the next stage is really integral for any new advisor joining the team here. It's the training and support stage. And so this is where you'll be enrolled in the Optimize Academy, where you'll learn how to use all of our core platforms and systems, such as our CRM, our portal, our portfolio reporting system, our payroll system, and our investment research tool. 00:14:33.930 --> 00:14:48.400 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: We'll also go through how to provide our various multifamily office services for your clients, so again, those complimentary tax returns, wills, powers of attorney, insurance help, mortgage help, all of those, will be within this stage as well. 00:14:48.660 --> 00:15:02.200 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And then another big part of the training and support stage is that, no matter where you are or what time it is, you'll be able to access our 24-7, live advisor support team. So these are live agents available to you 7 days a week, regardless of whether you're traveling or not. 00:15:02.200 --> 00:15:09.690 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: It's a really important part of the equation, as we want to ensure that you'll always have a live support member, regardless of whatever kind of comes up. 00:15:10.310 --> 00:15:31.129 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And then lastly, we'll get you started in that practice management program, as I mentioned before. This is where we'll look to streamline your current operations wherever possible. We'll also go through best practices with both our in-house practice management team, as well as a third-party experience consultant, all of which is to really focus on creating scalable strategies for you and your team. 00:15:31.130 --> 00:15:32.220 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Does that make sense? 00:15:32.520 --> 00:15:33.250 [ADVISOR]: does. 00:15:33.250 --> 00:15:33.980 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Great. 00:15:33.980 --> 00:15:58.090 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And then finally, the last stage is where you get to launch your transition. This is where you'll be able to track your progress every step of the way. You'll be able to see account openings, inbound transfers, as well as overall asset growth. And once you're up and running, it's really all about becoming a part of the optimized community. And so, accessing the advisor portal for daily research and company updates, getting regularly curated content on streamlining and growing your business. 00:15:58.150 --> 00:16:06.290 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Working with our practice management team and attending those regional and firm-wide conferences will all help work towards accomplishing that goal. 00:16:06.470 --> 00:16:17.089 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And really, one of the most important goals here for any advisor team that's transitioning to Optimize is to… we want to feel that you feel that you're every bit as part of our family, as well as our community. 00:16:19.280 --> 00:16:25.160 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And now, some key points here. There are some key critical success factors for any advisor transitioning. 00:16:25.450 --> 00:16:45.280 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And so it really begins with you fully implementing and personalizing that transition project plan that, that we'll put together for you. So, there'll be weekly check-in calls for ongoing deliverables to ensure that all of those milestones are met. At the beginning, it'll probably be more like daily or by, or every two days, just to make sure that 00:16:45.300 --> 00:16:52.020 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: We're getting that transition project plan all put together, and everything's kind of going smoothly. But then, once kind of things are sort of rolling, 00:16:52.030 --> 00:17:08.349 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: probably be more weekly. And as I should mention, while the heavy lifting is certainly done by our team, there are obvious deliverables, like getting your client data organized in advance of the transition, or working with our marketing team to ensure we have headshots and content for your website. These will obviously have to rest on your shoulders. 00:17:08.470 --> 00:17:24.020 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And then second, is enrolling and engaging with our advisor training and support system. So as you say, we really do get back what you put in, and so committing to accessing and leveraging all the training and support that we've created for you, is a really important part of this process as well. 00:17:24.839 --> 00:17:46.600 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And then thirdly, letting our client offering speak for itself, and what I mean by that is that there really are a number of key unique differentiators here at Optimize, and so we found that the best advisor transitions are the ones where the advisor really focuses their messaging on those key differentiators, so that their clients are best aware of all the additional value that we can collectively bring to their table. 00:17:46.750 --> 00:18:04.509 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And again, all of this is very much covered as part of the Optimize Academy, so you'll be very well versed in all those differentiators, but in short, sticking to what works has really… is what really… we really found what's best, in terms of, successful advisor transitions. And so… 00:18:04.640 --> 00:18:10.460 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Before I jump into our technology platform here, do you have any questions with regards to some of the information that, 00:18:11.020 --> 00:18:12.969 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That I kind of went over here with the transition? 00:18:13.210 --> 00:18:30.590 [A