ough our platform, and so think of all the time you'll save not having to spend time on calculating or processing trades. It's literally just point and click, and the account gets rebalanced, or money gets freed up for any EFTL request. 00:24:37.760 --> 00:25:01.879 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And then there's the re-entering existing client information. So, whether you're creating a financial plan or opening up a new account for an existing client, our platform automatically populates existing client information, so you'll never, there'll never be a need for you to re-enter dates of birth, or SWIP amounts, investment account values, or any other piece of existing client data. And so… and that goes on a two-way street, any financial plans or anything created through our 00:25:01.880 --> 00:25:08.079 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: financial planning software will be automatically put into HubSpot, where you'll be able to monitor everything again. 00:25:09.330 --> 00:25:17.460 [ADVISOR]: It's hard to imagine a platform where you don't have to enter the amount of details that we typically have to. 00:25:18.820 --> 00:25:36.869 [ADVISOR]: enter. I guess one thing that I would be interested to know, you know, in more detail, if possible, is how that works. I mean, I see, like, I see some images here of how it might look on my screen, but, 00:25:37.780 --> 00:25:46.289 [ADVISOR]: I don't know, it just seems… it just seems leaps and bounds ahead of, you know, what we're doing now, as far as, you know, the details. 00:25:46.730 --> 00:25:52.490 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, yeah, absolutely. I'll see if we can get, kind of a demo for you, in terms of, 00:25:52.490 --> 00:26:04.030 [ADVISOR]: Yeah, like a sandbox sort of thing. I don't know if you guys have sand… I mean, maybe you don't do sandbox for people who are applying for jobs with you guys, but, certainly, I mean, it's interesting because 00:26:04.030 --> 00:26:14.040 [ADVISOR]: you know, I mean, it's… it's different, and certainly different than… than I've used in the past, and… and if it does work the way it claims it works, I mean, it's… 00:26:14.230 --> 00:26:33.139 [ADVISOR]: you know, it should free up time for me to be doing, you know, putting my efforts into other places, which is something that every advisor is looking for. Everyone is looking for a way to take some of the back end off of their plate, so they can get out there and, you know, get in front of more clients and get in front of more prospects. 00:26:33.430 --> 00:26:34.350 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, yeah. 00:26:34.450 --> 00:26:53.990 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, absolutely. And so, yeah, our platform is, I think in 2023, we won Most Innovative Use of WealthTech, and then in 2024, I think we were runner-up. And so, yeah, in terms of cutting-edge technology, absolutely, it does work, if any piece of existing client information is there. 00:26:54.020 --> 00:27:04.559 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: it'll be populated in any kind of details, in any kind of reports, or anything you're trying to use. So yeah, it is actually one of the biggest benefits to our platform, and personally my favorite. 00:27:04.560 --> 00:27:21.189 [ADVISOR]: The data… sorry to interrupt you. When a beneficiary update is done, or a change is made, or something like that, and, you know, it's gone… it's going through this, you know, almost seamless, 00:27:21.700 --> 00:27:41.519 [ADVISOR]: back office that we're doing, do we get copies in addition to, you know, for our… for my portfolio, but just for our CRM, to make sure that… you know, I'm just used to having endless amounts of digital files for each… each client, for every single action that I make, so that my compliance is right, my note-taking is right. 00:27:41.740 --> 00:27:49.010 [ADVISOR]: Do we get copies sent to us of everything, or is it just stored in a centralized database somewhere? 00:27:49.010 --> 00:28:03.850 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So all… anything in terms of a, like, a beneficiary changes example, that document will be placed right on the