al large caps, mostly North American. 00:11:43.020 --> 00:11:55.100 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: On the other side, actively managed fixed income, and each one of our portfolios has about a 10 to, let's say, 20% maximum, 00:11:55.100 --> 00:12:00.390 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: pension-style asset sleep. Those… that comes through our relationships with 00:12:00.390 --> 00:12:25.149 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: 20 of the top managers in the world, KKRs, Apollos, Hamilton Lanes, you know, JP Morgan. Here in Canada, T.D. Greystone, Brookfield, as an example. And so that's, you know, our model is that everything, every advisor that we work with transitions, you know, everything into, into our five core models, so there isn't room in our modeling. 00:12:25.270 --> 00:12:39.070 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: to sort of play around the edges. And our advisors then lose that ability to select individual, securities, because we're a discretionary manager, licensed by the OSC, registered across Canada. 00:12:39.070 --> 00:12:55.359 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: We assign a portfolio manager to each one of our advisors. They operate in the background as their conduit to the Investment Management Committee, which is 7 PMs deep, supported by a team of quants, supported by a team of analysts. 00:12:55.360 --> 00:13:19.939 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: The only… the only time that PM has any interaction with clients is, in the onboarding process and, in the, and once a year for… for KYC. Otherwise, the advisor's front and center, does all the financial planning. The unique piece around what we do is two things. One is, that, pension-style asset sleeve in every 00:13:19.940 --> 00:13:34.970 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: one of our portfolios. The second is that we provide at no cost full family office services to every client, at no cost to the advisor, and on a personal level. And, 00:13:35.370 --> 00:13:38.659 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: At the same time, there are no account minimums. 00:13:39.330 --> 00:13:49.490 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So, it's available to every client across the entire book, right? So, obvious multi-generational, benefits there, so whether they're a 00:13:49.610 --> 00:14:05.859 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You know, and just to make the point, as an example, a $50 a month pack or a $5 million client, they're effectively getting the same access and the same management. So we were able to lift compliance from our advisors' shoulders completely as a result of our structure. 00:14:06.020 --> 00:14:07.050 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So… 00:14:07.440 --> 00:14:20.799 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, I can imagine if you didn't have compliance on your plate, to deal with. So, and we've got a 12-year… 12-year track record, with, with our models, 00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:33.950 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: just as a performance data point, our income portfolio, our most conservative portfolio, is… has a 9% since, inception return. 00:14:35.170 --> 00:14:42.449 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: the CRM that we, have put together, is, 00:14:42.450 --> 00:14:56.319 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: industry-leading as far as, our advisors are concerned. It's HubSpot, out of the box, but we've customized, I'm gonna say over 90% of it. We're HubSpot's largest, North American client. 00:14:56.370 --> 00:15:05.640 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: They use what we have developed for our channel specifically to market into the space, into this space, globally. Excuse me. 00:15:07.530 --> 00:15:25.699 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So, from a client's perspective, sort of 3 things change for clients, right? Better portfolios, they gain access to institutional-grade diversification and pension-style assets, and then, very much risk-mitigated construction. 00:15:25.990 --> 00:15:39.749 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: all designed to reduce volatility, deliver consistent long-term compounding. Second thing that is different is there is lower fees and barriers, so there are no account minimums, no admin fees, no transaction charges. 00:15:39.750 --> 00:15:57.939 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Clients keep more of their returns, and then those family office services at no additional cost. So wills