[ADVISOR]: [REGIONAL_COMMUNITY]. We summer at the [REGIONAL_LAKE_AREA] every summer as well. 00:03:22.730 --> 00:03:25.879 [OPTIMIZE REP]: Oh, there you go. Yeah, yeah, we were on [REGIONAL_LAKE_AREA]. 00:03:26.490 --> 00:03:28.670 [ADVISOR]: They're both nice. They're both nice. 00:03:28.670 --> 00:03:47.439 [OPTIMIZE REP]: Fantastic. Well, listen, good to visit with you, both. Nice way to finish up a Friday. Just by way of quick formal introduction, again, my name is [OPTIMIZE REP], Managing Director of Corporate Development here at Optimize Financial Group. 00:03:47.440 --> 00:03:51.679 [OPTIMIZE REP]: Just to set the tone for our conversation, I'd just like to take a minute and 00:03:51.680 --> 00:04:05.030 [OPTIMIZE REP]: You know, we're going to just spend a little bit of time at a high level. I'll show you… I'll give you an overview of our institutional asset management platform, and how we're really helping established advisors 00:04:05.030 --> 00:04:16.890 [OPTIMIZE REP]: substantially elevate their client outcomes, earn significantly more income, and build enterprise value. And when the time comes, set up a much stronger, smoother. 00:04:16.890 --> 00:04:31.629 [OPTIMIZE REP]: And, I'd say considerably more lucrative retirement or exit from the business. We're not chasing books, we're not trying to push volume through the door here. We're fully independent. We're very intentional about who we speak with. 00:04:31.670 --> 00:04:48.290 [OPTIMIZE REP]: We don't run a rookie program, so we're only engaging with experienced, values-aligned advisors, folks with a really strong history of performance, a great reputation in the industry, and most importantly, and this is really the key for us, is a client-first mindset. 00:04:48.320 --> 00:05:07.370 [OPTIMIZE REP]: And that's really non-negotiable. That's the qualitative characteristic that we've really built the, our advisor base on. So this is a very patient, multi-stage process, so there's zero pressure or obligation here on either side. 00:05:07.370 --> 00:05:21.120 [OPTIMIZE REP]: It's… so just think of this really as a very exploratory process for both of us, as it ought to be. If we feel a little bit of alignment today, next step would be to book a little follow-up session in, you know, the next week or 10 days. 00:05:21.120 --> 00:05:31.140 [OPTIMIZE REP]: And that's where we'd walk through a dealer analysis report that we'd put together. I'd have the team put together, quantifies the value lift to your clients and to your business. 00:05:31.470 --> 00:05:46.159 [OPTIMIZE REP]: We'd take a look, a little bit closer look at our investment philosophy, risk metrics, and performance. If still things, if we're still feeling a bit of alignment from there, we'd share more insight into our transition program and our technology stack. 00:05:46.190 --> 00:06:00.629 [OPTIMIZE REP]: And our sport model. And ultimately, again, based on, you know, sort of emerging alignment, we'd extend an invitation to bring you to [HEAD_OFFICE_CITY], to our head office, for an in-person mutual due diligence. 00:06:00.630 --> 00:06:12.220 [OPTIMIZE REP]: session with, with our senior leadership, and that's a key piece of the puzzle, just in the exploration phases for all of us, so we look after those costs and just as. 00:06:12.220 --> 00:06:15.230 [ADVISOR]: It had a business expense for us. 00:06:15.230 --> 00:06:17.500 [OPTIMIZE REP]: But we really feel like that, 00:06:17.560 --> 00:06:26.219 [OPTIMIZE REP]: You know, before we would even consider extending an invitation to join us, that's a really key piece. 00:06:26.220 --> 00:06:39.159 [OPTIMIZE REP]: So there's no obligation through any of that on either side, up to and including through the due diligence process. So having said that, I'd just like to… does that seem reasonable as at least a foundation for today's call? 00:06:39.380 --> 00:06:40.230 [ADVISOR]: Nope. 00:06:40.230 --> 00:06:55.049 [OPTIMIZE REP]: Yeah, fair enough. So, just