rtion is increasing. I'm not so sure on the independent side. I think it's staying… 00:17:41.919 --> 00:17:49.649 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: If anything, just kind of more so the conversation has been around, we're gonna look into it, as opposed to actual changes. 00:17:49.650 --> 00:17:51.009 [ADVISOR]: I would have asked [PERSON]? 00:17:51.460 --> 00:17:52.779 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, I have not. 00:17:53.150 --> 00:17:53.970 [ADVISOR]: Okay. 00:17:53.970 --> 00:17:54.350 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay. 00:17:54.350 --> 00:17:59.449 [ADVISOR]: It's like a platform where advisors go and buy and sell books. 00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:04.700 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, and again, this is obviously [CURRENT_DEALER] Advisors as well, that you can. 00:18:04.700 --> 00:18:08.059 [ADVISOR]: I don't think so, I think it's extra outside of [CURRENT_DEALER]. 00:18:08.060 --> 00:18:14.920 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, and this is some… a potential opportunity for you to essentially institutionalize outside assets within [CURRENT_DEALER], correct? 00:18:14.920 --> 00:18:18.550 [ADVISOR]: And perhaps if you want to look into… I don't want to be competing with you buying books, but… 00:18:18.550 --> 00:18:24.490 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, no, no, of course, and we welcome it, right? We facilitate those transactions, and what we're saying is. 00:18:24.490 --> 00:18:40.259 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You can buy a book, certainly, right? Even as an optimized advisor, and ultimately would kind of follow this traditional approach in terms of what we pay as compensation for those assets to arrive on our books, right? 00:18:40.260 --> 00:18:42.099 [ADVISOR]: How long do they have to stay there for? 00:18:42.180 --> 00:18:49.940 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So, 7 to 8 years. This kind of prevents gaming of the system for advisors just coming over, collecting their transition bonus, and moving on. 00:18:50.180 --> 00:18:52.570 [ADVISOR]: What if I don't want to work for 7 or 8 more years? 00:18:53.000 --> 00:19:00.479 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: So that's fine. Again, if you, announce a succession, in which 00:19:00.480 --> 00:19:22.579 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, within the first 5 years, you'll get that full 5%. That's the criteria for that full 5% being paid. It is prorated, as long as the book is not leaving optimized, and it's being either, you know, there's a legacy component attached to your succession plan in terms of maybe a son or daughter taking over the business, usually the case, 90-95% of the times, it's a son or daughter taking… 00:19:22.580 --> 00:19:26.960 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: And I get it, but you'll have the opportunity to, 00:19:27.100 --> 00:19:33.799 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, have a conversation in terms of what that succession option looks like internally at Optimize, okay? And if it's. 00:19:33.800 --> 00:19:37.199 [ADVISOR]: So you only get that succession if you leave within 5 years? 00:19:37.200 --> 00:19:42.310 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's correct. And it's prorated, I think I have a scale here. 00:19:42.610 --> 00:19:44.850 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Not sure if you're… 00:19:45.800 --> 00:20:04.740 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, so 5 or more years would qualify for that full 5% succession payout, but again, you know, in that year as well, if any new business being… is written, it's 5 years or more. So a blended rate of 7. All we're saying is, if you choose to retire within that first year, obviously there wouldn't be a clawback to that transition bonus, because the book has not left. 00:20:04.770 --> 00:20:20.989 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: But what we're saying is, you know, successor payout of 2.5%, not 2.5 times, right? So we take that snapshot of the, you know, the valuation of that book of business, and then pay you accordingly, right? So a blended rate in that year would look like something like a 4.5%. 00:20:21.140 --> 00:20:32.190 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: In terms of total compensation. And that kind of excludes that trailer fee component, right? Of that 1%, but again, that would be added to this, would probably be 5, 5.5%. 00:20:32.190 --> 00:20:51