growth. 00:39:53.610 --> 00:39:59.590 [ADVISOR]: So there's only 5… I don't want to say fund posts, because there's corporate class… maybe? Is there corporate class on the bridge? 00:39:59.590 --> 00:40:00.200 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yo. 00:40:00.200 --> 00:40:01.420 [ADVISOR]: No corporate class for now. 00:40:01.420 --> 00:40:03.270 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: corporate class. Yeah, and that's fine. 00:40:03.270 --> 00:40:04.300 [ADVISOR]: we're targeting. 00:40:04.590 --> 00:40:05.800 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's correct. 00:40:06.730 --> 00:40:08.829 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Sorry, the market that we're targeting? 00:40:08.830 --> 00:40:16.600 [ADVISOR]: The market we're targeting is non-REG funds, really, because we want people that have maxed out their RRSPs and maxed out their TFSAs and have nowhere else to put it but non-REG. 00:40:16.600 --> 00:40:17.159 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, no, no. 00:40:17.160 --> 00:40:18.370 [ADVISOR]: Gotcha. 00:40:18.370 --> 00:40:18.970 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Perfectly. 00:40:19.640 --> 00:40:26.030 [ADVISOR]: Part of a real tool to help that market is corporate class funds, but we don't have any, and we're trying to target that market, is that right? 00:40:26.030 --> 00:40:26.850 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's correct. 00:40:26.850 --> 00:40:27.720 [ADVISOR]: Okay. 00:40:27.910 --> 00:40:36.659 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Yeah, we do not have… and again, our philosophy there has been, you know, some of the structures that have been long-standing within corporate class funds have been eroded. Yeah. 00:40:36.660 --> 00:41:00.739 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: closed loopholes, or whatever that might be, through successive budget announcements, and so a big foray into offering a corporate class fund and potentially creating a different cost structure, didn't seem viable internally to pursue, okay? And again, from our end, you know, just really looking at it, holistically and, 00:41:00.740 --> 00:41:04.130 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: You know, when we talk about, 00:41:04.250 --> 00:41:27.840 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, our institutional models, right? I like to use the analogy of a barbell, right? And on one side of that barbell, high-quality, you know, large-cap public equities, that equity side will always have a bias towards, you know, high-quality blue-chip companies, you know, strong earnings and balance sheets, industry leaders running them. On the other side, we talk about, you know, again, just to kind of give you a snapshot of 00:41:27.840 --> 00:41:40.609 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, how our portfolio methodology or construction of these portfolios. You know, on the other side of that barbell, we talk about, you know, actively managed fixed income, as well as pension-style asset classes. 00:41:40.610 --> 00:42:05.310 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Again, that simply aren't available to retail investors, right? And again, you know, think of private equity and private credit, infrastructure and real estate. These are tools utilized within these pension-style asset classes to, again, give you that growth profile, if you will, but significantly reducing volatility, right? And again, you know, when we look at some of the pension managers that we have access 00:42:05.310 --> 00:42:08.450 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: do, you know, Apollo, Goldman Sachs, 00:42:08.450 --> 00:42:27.670 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, KKR in the United States, we have Brookfield Asset Management, Fiera Capital, TD Greystone. Again, these are… it's not a comprehensive list, but again, just some of the partners, that, that, that we deal with. I just want to kind of list that out. But again, from our… 00:42:27.670 --> 00:42:32.170 [ADVISOR]: Is there fee-based and commission-based codes for each of the five portfolios? 00:42:32.170 --> 00:42:33.670 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: No, just fee-based. 00:42:33.940 --> 00:42:34.630 [ADVISOR]: Okay? 00:42:34.630 --> 00:42:54.399 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Just fee-based, and when we talk about, you know, our fees, we're talking about a 1.45 account level fee, and then that's coupled with a 70 basis point F-class or fund-level fee on any of our institutional models, okay? So income and equity are the same price to own? 00:42:54.400 --> 00:42:55.270 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That's correct. 00:42:55.500 --> 00:42:56.160 [ADVISOR]: Okay. 00:42:56.160 --> 00:43:00.709 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Okay, so 2.15 all in, but again, going back to your point, it's decoupled. 00:43:00.710 --> 00:43:25.670 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: That fee alone is very compelling when you look at what an average retail MER is, right? An actively managed retail MER. But again, it's not one lump sum in terms of an MER. We've decoupled it, making it that much more tax-efficient for non-registered accounts, and providing, you know, tax deductibility, right? And again, from our endpoint, it's just really easy to look at and say, you know, another core value that we offer 00:43:25.670 --> 00:43:30.140 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: for advisors, and kind of, you know, really, it's a hand-holding process all the way through. 00:43:30.140 --> 00:43:52.380 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: Whereas it might feel, and it might not be for you specifically, but for most advisors, especially coming from [CURRENT_DEALER], they might feel like a number, right? And from our end, it's really personalized. It's really looking at the advisor's profile, advisor's book of business, and how we speak to them, in terms of how we integrate them, and then how we get them 00:43:52.520 --> 00:44:12.760 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: you know, most institutions is to get them to the goal line, right? We tell you that we get you past… and that's kind of our promise, right? We get you past that goal line. And again, you know, we look at our next generation marketing and support, right? We know one of the biggest pain points for advisors is, you know, clients leaving them, and one of the reasons that that happens is… 00:44:12.760 --> 00:44:36.569 [OPTIMIZE_REP]: their lack of visibility, right? So, you know, our marketing team really kind of puts together, you know, engaging content to keep you front and center with those